===Etymology===
English ''[[walk]]'' + ''[[man]]''. The product name '''walkman''' was made up for a portable audio cassette player by Sony Corporation which went on sale in Japan on July 1, 1979. '''Walkman''' remains to be a trademark of Sony in many countries, though it is now also used for portable audio cassette players from other manufacturers.

